css
you style html elements using the following tags
1.id : Style specific element with the id
2.class: groups a styling and associate it with any element falling within the class
3.element name: styles any elements without an id or class

we have three forms of css
1.internal
css is written inside the html file
2.external
css is written outside th html file
3.inline
css is written using the style attribute inside the html
